rms, and making compliance easier. Concerned with these choices, the IRS asked the National Academy to assess previous research on the determinants of taxpayer compliance and to highlight the most promising areas for future research. The Academy's panel authored the two-volume Taxpayer Compliance. Volume I presents the panel's report, which critically reviews previous research on the subject, reaches conclusions about the findings, and recommends future research programs to fill gaps in knowledge. The report also recommends ways to maintain and develop the intellectual, financial, and data resources devoted to taxpayer compliance research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aTaxationxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 0aTaxpayer compliancezUnited States. 7aLAW / Taxation.2bisacsh  aBusiness.  aEconomics.  aPublic Policy.1 aBoruch, Robert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoth, Jeffrey A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScholz, John T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSehmidt, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWitte, Ann Dryden, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999z978311044252640uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/978151280627440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781512806274423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781512806274.jpg  a978-3-11-044252-6  University of Pennsylvania Press Package Archive 1898-1999c1898d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12S